  "narrative": {
    "intro": "Federal contract obligations in Nebraska totaled $902M in FY2026 to date. Contracting activity produced 12,819 awards with an average award size of $70.3K, and obligations are down 28.8% year over year. The Department of Defense accounted for $321M of obligations and the Department of Education accounted for $289M, together representing the largest buying agencies in the state by dollar value. At the vendor level, NELNET SERVICING LLC received $289M and GENERAL DYNAMICS INFORMATION TECHNOLOGY, INC. received $121M. The largest industry category by obligations was Other Activities Related to Credit Intermediation at $289M, followed by Computer Systems Design Services at $154M. These figures are fiscal year to date and current-year totals are partial (fiscal year to date).",
    "sections": [
      {
        "heading": "Which agencies dominate federal contracting in Nebraska?",
        "body": "The Department of Defense led buying in Nebraska with $321M in obligations, followed by the Department of Education with $289M. The General Services Administration contributed $132M, and the Department of Veterans Affairs contributed $78M. Smaller buying agencies in the top ten include the Department of Agriculture at $23M and the Department of Transportation at $3.1M."
      },
      {
        "heading": "What do the top vendors and industry categories look like in Nebraska?",
        "body": "NELNET SERVICING LLC was the largest vendor with $289M in obligations, and GENERAL DYNAMICS INFORMATION TECHNOLOGY, INC. was the second largest with $121M. Other leading vendors include HENDRICKSON TRANSPORTATION LLC at $43.7M and S365 INC at $34.1M. The largest industry categories were Other Activities Related to Credit Intermediation at $289M and Computer Systems Design Services at $154M."
      }
    ]
  },
